  <div class="postcards-container">

    <!-- Postcard #1: Neo vs Agents -->
    <div class="postcard">
      <div class="postcard-inner">
        <!-- Front -->
        <div class="postcard-front">
          <%= image_tag "postcards/neo-agents.png", alt: "AI as Extension", class: "postcard-image" %>
        </div>

        <!-- Back -->
        <div class="postcard-back">
          <div class="postcard-content">
            <div class="postcard-text">
              <p>One of the dominant mental models in AI: "digital assistants." External agents you hire to do things, so you don't have to think about them anymore.</p>

              <p>Personally, something feels off when I use AI that way. It's like having robot arms hammer piano keys. Technically impressive. But it's not me playing.</p>

              <p>Instead, I think of AI as my own extension. I'm painstakingly steering it at first, willing a high quality bar into existence...then it gradually becomes second nature.</p>

              <p>It's less like being "served", and more like defying gravity with my new kung fu program.</p>

              <p class="postcard-signature">You feel me?</p>
            </div>

            <div class="postcard-meta">
              <div class="postcard-date">Oct 11, 2025</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
